1.title: Star Wars Parody "Sand People"

episode of.title: The Carrot and Potato Show (TV Series 2015– )

1.plot: The Carrot and Potato Show proudly presents: Star Wars "Sand People" So apparently, when referring to the Tusken Raider's as "Sand People" isn't all that politically correct. Carrot and Potato head on down to the dune sea on the planet Tatooine and come across a sand crawler and a group of slaughtered Jawas. They are accompanied by Obi-Wan Kenobi, Luke Skywalker, and R2-D2, and find out the hard way, that one should never refer to a Tusken Raider as Sand People. This is based off of Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope. All characters and similarities to movies appearing ...

3.title: Star Wars Parody "Death Star"

episode of.title: The Carrot and Potato Show (TV Series 2015– )

3.plot: This is what happens when you don't use the force. Taking down a Death Star is hard work. Thankfully, the Star Wars universe contains the energy force that surrounds and binds us enough to get a torpedo to travel inside a small hole no bigger than a womp rat. But what happens when Luke Skywalker decides to not use the force and rely on the expensive, well designed equipment known as the targeting scanner in his X wing? Watch and find out.

4.title: Mad Max: Fury Road Parody "Blood Bags"

episode of.title: The Carrot and Potato Show (TV Series 2015– )

4.plot: Get a nice front row seat in your very own pursuit car, straight out of Mad Max: Fury Road. Sure they'll need you to be a "Blood Bag", and you might be in the most dangerous seat. But come on. Who wouldn't want to take part in a Mad Max raid, or even just a friendly trip to your local Gas Town or Bullet Farm.
